# Pre-Commit Quality Checks

Before staging and committing **any** code change, all three of the following checks must pass locally. Never commit code that fails any of them.

## Required Checks (run in this order)

### 1. Tests
```bash
pnpm test
```
Runs Jest across all workspaces via Turborepo. All existing tests must remain green. New code must be covered by tests written in the TDD cycle (see `tdd.mdc`).

### 2. Type-check
```bash
pnpm typecheck
```
Runs `tsc --noEmit` in every app/package. Zero TypeScript errors are acceptable — do not use `// @ts-ignore` or `// @ts-expect-error` to silence errors without a documented reason.

### 3. Biome (lint + format)
```bash
pnpm check
```
Runs `biome check .` from the repo root, covering linting **and** formatting for all `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.js`, `.mjs`, `.jsx`, and `.json` files.

To auto-fix safe issues (formatting and safe lint fixes) before the check:
```bash
pnpm format          # biome format --write .
pnpm check --write   # biome check --write . (applies safe fixes)
```

## The Pre-Commit Sequence

Run these commands from the repo root before every `git commit`:

```bash
pnpm test && pnpm typecheck && pnpm check
```

All three must exit with code `0`. If any step fails:
1. Fix the reported issues.
2. Re-run the full sequence from the beginning.
3. Do not proceed to `git commit` until the sequence passes cleanly end-to-end.

## Key Configuration Locations

| Tool | Config |
|---|---|
| Biome (lint + format) | `/workspace/biome.json` |
| TypeScript (root base) | `/workspace/tsconfig.base.json` |
| TypeScript (backend) | `/workspace/apps/backend/tsconfig.json` |
| TypeScript (frontend) | `/workspace/apps/frontend/tsconfig.json` |
| Jest (backend unit) | inline in `/workspace/apps/backend/package.json` |
| Jest (backend e2e) | `/workspace/apps/backend/test/jest-e2e.json` |
| Turborepo pipeline | `/workspace/turbo.json` |

## Notes

- The `pnpm check` command at the repo root runs Biome across the entire monorepo in one pass, which is faster than running per-app.
- Turborepo caches task outputs — if nothing has changed, `pnpm test` and `pnpm typecheck` will return instantly from cache. This is expected behaviour, not a skipped check.
- Do not bypass these checks with `--no-verify` on `git commit` unless directed to do so explicitly by the user.
